pr_body:
@dhermes mentioned this in a previous review.
This is correct and I also cleaned up the docs.

In my testing with async, I haven't gotten more than one alternative to show up, even whith `max_alternatives=2`. So that's why there isn't two in the doc example.

Follow-up to today's releases.

Has #4500 as diffbase.

@lukesneeringer Do we have a tag for the "uber"-package / umbrella-package?

for refs see:

https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/influxdb/yWpv_WJ6-uU
https://github.com/influxdb/influxdb/issues/2124

This PR provides an easier API to process data returned by Splash.

TODO:

* [ ] fix saving/loading Splash responses to/from cache;
* [ ] magical JSON response handling:
  * [ ] set response.headers from 'headers';
  * [ ] set response.body either from 'html' or 'body';
  * [ ] set response.status from 'http_status';
  * [ ] set response.url from 'url.
* [ ] add shortcuts to access base64-encoded values (e.g. 'png' / 'jpeg' keys);
* [ ] re-check that SplashRequest works correctly with persistent request queues.
* [ ] check how custom Splash responses interact with builtin Scrapy middlewares, esp. when headers are restored from JSON response:
  * [ ] RetryMiddleware;
  * [ ] AjaxCrawlMiddleware;
  * [ ] ChunkedTransferMiddleware;
  * [ ] DecompressionMiddleware;
  * [ ] HttpCompressionMiddleware;
  * [ ] RedirectMiddleware;
  * [ ] RobotsTxtMiddleware;
  * [ ] RefererMiddleware

See https://github.com/scrapy-plugins/scrapy-splash/issues/44, https://github.com/scrapy-plugins/scrapy-splash/issues/14, https://github.com/scrapy-plugins/scrapy-splash/issues/12, https://github.com/scrapy-plugins/scrapy-splash/issues/10, https://github.com/scrapy-plugins/scrapy-splash/issues/8.
